cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel method that involves training a CNN classifier in a fully convolutional manner, which falls under the domain of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also involves designing a process to stimulate peaks to emerge from a class response map, which involves some level of algorithmic design and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also reports state-of-the-art results on popular benchmarks, which falls under the domain of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves back-propagation and mapping of peaks to highly informative regions of each object instance, which involves some level of neural network optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
